28/03/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Three crew members of a Turkish cargo ship were injured after a pirate attack off the coast of Nigeria, local media reported on Friday (March 26th). Two of the injured are Turkish citizens, the third is Nigerian. Up to ten armed pirates attacked the ship late Thursday, grabbing the crew's money and mobile phones. Scuffles broke out after a crew member pressed an alarm button. (Reuters, UPI, Anadolu news agency - 26/03/10)
